name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 28, a man accused Jiangsu Satellite TV of malicious editing. The man said that Jiangsu Satellite TV interviewed him, "When relatives asked him some offensive questions, how would you answer?" The man said that his answer at the time was "Maybe others will say that my affairs have nothing to do with you, but I won't say that. I will communicate with my elders in a friendly manner." As a result, Jiangsu Satellite TV edited out "My affairs have nothing to do with you" and misinterpreted the man's original intention. https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1885363638120439808/pu/img/N3CClKHaF9RCrX47.jpg

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 31, US Secretary of State Rubio said in an interview with Megyn Kelly that he did not hear Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi warn him to "be careful" during a call. 
"But they like to play this trick, saying one thing in English and another in Chinese, but at least I didn't hear it, otherwise I would say the same thing... But it's boring and irrelevant. What really matters is our future decisions" https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1885493828167081984/pu/img/dl5ycOqHqqUQz1P4.jpg

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
U.S. Secretary of State Rubio said in an interview with Megan Kelly: I didn't hear Minister Wang warn me to "be careful" during the call.
Megyn Kelly: There are reports that you received some kind of warning to "be careful"
Rubio: "Yes, someone told me about it. ... I didn't, at least the translator on the call didn't say anything to me that I thought was excessive. ... They like to do this, say one thing in English and then translate it into another. They never say anything like that. ... At least it didn't happen on the call, or at least their translator might not want to translate it that way. "

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
The U.S. Department of Justice said John Rogers, 63, a former Federal Reserve economist, was arrested on Friday and charged with conspiring to pass sensitive information to people working for the Chinese government.
The indictment unsealed Friday in federal court in Washington, D.C., alleges that economist John Harold Rogers lied to investigators as the Fed investigated his relationship with a Chinese national who claimed to be a graduate student at a Chinese university.
Rogers served as a senior adviser at the Fed's international finance division in Washington from 2010 to 2021. He joined the Fed's economist team in 1994, according to a resume on his personal website. After leaving the Fed, he taught at Fudan University in Shanghai.
A Fed spokesman declined to comment. Rogers could not be reached for comment Friday afternoon.
